The '''''To Harp at Twilight''''' was a [[book]] penned by [[Storm Silverhand]], a [[Harper]] and a [[Chosen]] of [[Mystra]], in the early 13{{th}} century [[DR]].

{{quote|''Try as we may, none of us can be in all places at all times. Not even the [[god]]s can do that. So we do what we can and measure our success, if we are wise, by what our hearts tell us at the end of a day, and not what our eyes tell us of how much we have changed [[Faer√ªn]].''|Excerpt from ''To Harp at Twilight''}}
